#. Tag: para
#: epoch.docbook:10
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An epoch is a certain instant of time (usually past) used as a reference for "
"time measurement in astronomy. In order to make calculations easier, "
"astronomers usually use the number of days that have passed since a certain "
"moment in time as a way of representing time in astronomical calculations. "
"This arbitrarily chosen \"starting point\" reference for time is called an "
"epoch."
msgstr ""
"Epoha je določen trenutek časa (običajno pretekli), ki se uporablja kot "
"referenca za merjenje časa v astronomiji. Da bi si olajšali izračune, "
"astronomi običajno uporabljajo število dni, ki so pretekli od določenega "
"trenutka, kot način za predstavitev časa v astronomskih izračunih. To "
"poljubno izbrano referenco \"izhodiščne točke\" za čas imenujemo epoha."

#. Tag: para
#: epoch.docbook:18
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An epoch is usually cited along with <link linkend=\"equatorial\">equatorial "
"coordinates</link> in astronomical catalogs, since the equatorial "
"coordinates of sky objects change (although slowly) with time. Printed star "
"charts / atlases are usually marked as being valid for a certain epoch."
msgstr ""
"Epoha se v astronomskih katalogih običajno navaja skupaj z <link linkend="
"\"equatorial\">ekvatorialnimi koordinatami</link>, saj se ekvatorialne "
"koordinate nebesnih objektov s časom spreminjajo (čeprav počasi). Tiskane "
"zvezdne karte/atlasi so običajno označene kot veljavne za določeno obdobje."

#. Tag: para
#: epoch.docbook:26
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The most popular epoch used currently is J2000.0, (the <link linkend=\"ai-"
"julianday\">Julian year</link> 2000.0), which (almost exactly) corresponds "
"to 1st January 2000, 12:00 noon UTC. Other epochs include B1900 and B1950."
msgstr ""
"Trenutno najbolj priljubljena uporabljena epoha je J2000.0 (<link linkend="
"\"ai-julianday\">Julijansko leto</link> 2000.0), ki (skoraj natančno) "
"ustreza 1. januarju 2000, 12:00 opoldne UTC. Druge epohe vključujejo B1900 "
"in B1950."

#. Tag: para
#: epoch.docbook:32
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kstars; supports catalogs based on J2000.0 and B1950.0 epochs."
msgstr "&kstars; podpira kataloge, ki temeljijo na epohah J2000.0 in B1950.0."
